ns31:Activity.ns31:ActivityDescription:
Get close to the action and explore the Daytona International Speedway on this informative, private, guided tour. Journey behind the scenes and get an up-close look at the mecca of auto racing.
Enjoy a privately guided tour around the Daytona track and step into the rich history of the International Speedway. Learn about the $400-million renovation project as you travel through the updated racetrack. Explore the "Velocitorium", home to Sir Malcolm Campbell’s Bluebird V, the historic 28-foot, 10,000-pound automobile that set a land speed record of 276.82 mph back in 1935.
Put the enormity of this track in its proper perspective and witness the 31-degree angled banks that these battle-tested professional drivers face. Experience what it's like to be in the driver's meeting room, tour the Heritage Museum, and access the Coca-Cola Theater for a close-up look at the Daytona 500 Champion Car. Leave with a new-found respect for the track, the cars, and the excitement of speed.
